{LIVESTOCK.}
HERDS OF{FRIESIAN}COWS ARE KEPT AND THE ROYAL AGRICULTURAL COLLEGE HAS USED CANADIAN{HOLSTEIN}BULLS AS WELL AS FRIESIAN BULLS TO IMPROVE THE HERD. THE AIM IS TO EASE MILKING PROBLEMS AND TO LENGTHEN THE COWS' LIFE. MOST BEEF-CALVES ARE OF THE FREISIAN OR FRIESIAN/HOLSTEIN TYPE BUT A{HEREFORD} BULL IS USED ON A FEW OF THE COWS AND HEIFERS.THE LATTER ARE SOLD AS IN-CALF HEIFERS.
THE COLLEGE HAS A FLOCK OF SHEEP, MAINLY MULES AND WELSH HALFBRED EWES WITH LARGELY SUFFOLK RAMS. LAMBING TAKES PLACE IN LATE FEBRUARY AND EARLY MARCH.
